  "5-12": (
    caption: [DNA ligase joins together Okazaki fragments on the lagging strand during DNA synthesis. The ligase enzyme uses a molecule of ATP to activate the 5′ phosphate of one fragment (step 1) before forming a new bond with the 3′ hydroxyl of the other fragment (step 2). 5′ phosphate],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
