  "5-14": (
    caption: [The structure of a DNA helicase. (A) Diagram of the protein, a hexameric ring, drawn to scale with a replication fork. (B) Detailed structure of the bacteriophage T7 replicative helicase, as determined by x-ray diffraction. Six identical subunits bind and hydrolyze ATP in an ordered fashion to propel this molecule, like a rotary engine, along a DNA single strand that passes through the central hole. Bound ATP molecules in the structure are indicated in red (Movie 5.2). (PDB code: 1E0J.) (B)],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
