  "5-15": (
    caption: [The effect of single-strand DNA-binding proteins (SSB proteins) on the structure of single-stranded DNA. Because each protein molecule prefers to bind next to a previously bound molecule, long rows of this protein form on a DNA single strand. This cooperative binding straightens out the DNA template and facilitates the DNA polymerization process. The “hairpin helices” shown in the bare, single-stranded DNA result from a chance matching of short regions of complementary nucleotide sequence.],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
